<Project>

  <!--
    Backend Sprint 3 quality gate: warnings-as-errors.

    All compiler (CSxxxx), analyzer (CAxxxx), and code-style (IDExxxx)
    warnings fail the build. Forces real fixes instead of accumulating
    silent warnings.

    Permanent exclusions (never blocking, no follow-up):
    - NU1901..NU1904: NuGet package vulnerability advisories. These can
      surface without any code change (a transitive dep gains a CVE
      overnight) and are the responsibility of the dep-upgrade track,
      not of the MR that happens to be open at the time. Tracked
      separately under docs/QUALITY-SECURITY-PLAN.md.
    - CS8981: "type name only contains lower-case ASCII chars". Fires
      on EF Core's auto-generated migration class names (e.g.
      'productsides', 'special'). Migrations are immutable once
      applied to staging/prod (CLAUDE.md §9), so renaming is not an
      option. The warning surfaces nothing actionable here.

    Transitional exclusions (Sprint 3, follow-up MRs to clear):
    - CS8600/CS8601/CS8602/CS8604: nullable-reference warnings — 16
      sites flagged at gate-flip time, each needs careful per-site
      null-handling review. Tracked as a follow-up issue.
    - ASPDEPR002: 4 uses of the deprecated WithOpenApi() API in
      Program.cs; minimal-API OpenAPI was renamed in .NET 10.
      Tracked as a follow-up.
    These exclusions should be removed once the follow-up MRs land.
  -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>
    <WarningsNotAsErrors>
      NU1901;NU1902;NU1903;NU1904;
      CS8981;
      CS8600;CS8601;CS8602;CS8604;ASPDEPR002
    </WarningsNotAsErrors>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
